@startuml reusable-workflow-relationships
title Reusable Workflow Relationships: Standard Stack Composition

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam ArrowColor #333333
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam component {
  BackgroundColor<<caller>> #E3F2FD
  BackgroundColor<<bundle>> #E8F5E9
  BackgroundColor<<composed>> #FFF3E0
  BackgroundColor<<alt>> #E0E0E0
  BorderColor #666666
}

package "Consumer Repository (generic Python project)" {
  [Caller Workflow\n(e.g. .github/workflows/ci.yml)] <<caller>> as caller
}

[python-standard-stack.yml\n(bundling layer)] <<bundle>> as stack

package "Composed by the Standard Stack (verified from jobs:)" {
  [python-ci.yml\n(job: ci)] <<composed>> as ci
  [python-security-analysis.yml\n(job: security, needs: ci)] <<composed>> as security
  [python-sbom.yml\n(job: sbom, needs: ci)] <<composed>> as sbom
  [python-snyk.yml\n(job: snyk, needs: ci,\nconditional: if inputs.run-snyk)] <<composed>> as snyk
}

package "Other Reusable Workflows\n(called directly by consumers, outside the bundle)" {
  [python-snyk-iac.yml] <<alt>> as snykiac
  [python-publish-pypi.yml] <<alt>> as pypi
  [python-sonarcloud.yml] <<alt>> as sonar
}

caller --> stack : uses (workflow_call)
stack --> ci : always
stack --> security : needs: ci
stack --> sbom : needs: ci
stack ..> snyk : needs: ci\nif: inputs.run-snyk

caller ..> snykiac : uses directly\n(advanced config)
caller ..> pypi : uses directly\n(OIDC publish)
caller ..> sonar : uses directly\n(needs SONAR_TOKEN)

note right of stack
  **Source:**
  - .github/workflows/python-standard-stack.yml

  Nesting depth: caller (1) -> standard-stack (2) ->
  python-ci / python-security-analysis / python-sbom /
  python-snyk (3). python-snyk's own jobs are not nested
  reusable calls, so this stays within GitHub's 4-level
  reusable workflow limit.
end note

note bottom of snykiac
  **Source (catalog):**
  - README.md, "Available Workflows" table
  - .github/workflows/python-snyk-iac.yml
  - .github/workflows/python-publish-pypi.yml
  - .github/workflows/python-sonarcloud.yml

  Called directly by consumer repos that need advanced
  or matrix configuration the standard stack does not
  expose (per python-standard-stack.yml's own comment:
  "For advanced configuration ... call the individual
  workflows directly").
end note

@enduml
